article.description: Florida A&M romps over Edward Waters 104-69
article.headline: Florida A&M romps over Edward Waters 104-69
article.linkText: Florida A&M romps over Edward Waters 104-69
article.story:
TALAHASSEE, Fla. --  Florida A&M defeated Edward Waters 104-69 on Wednesday night to extend its winning streak to four games.

The Rattlers (12-16, 7-7 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) took a 54-32 lead over the Tigers at halftime, getting at least 50 points in each half.

It was the second time this season Florida A&M had reached the century mark. The Rattlers defeated Florida Memorial 100-82 on Nov. 30.

Florida A&M returns to MEAC play with two regular-season games remaining, playing at Morgan State before coming home to face Bethune-Cookman.

Edward Waters is an NAIA school in Jacksonville, Fla.
